org.tagaprice.server.service.helper
Class EntityCreator

java.lang.Object
  org.tagaprice.server.service.helper.EntityCreator

public class EntityCreator
extends java.lang.Object

This class is used for testing purposes only. Entities can freshly created, i.e. new objects will be created with each call, by calling the various create methods. This class is not hibernate session save, so two calls may create the same object with the same identifier, which leads - running it in a hibernate session - to a hibernate exceptions. Use HibernateSaveEntityCreator instead to have hibernate save objects.

Author:
"forste"
